wikipedia_page.main: Gloria Gwendolyn Lycett was a British figure skater. She competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics, the first Olympics where figure skating was contested, and finished fifth out of five skaters.  She also participated at the World Figure Skating Championships twice, finishing fourth in 1912.
